-- Russia, India Discuss Plan to Build Stealth Plane, Su-30 Fighter Jet Sales
-- B y   L y u b o v   P r o n i n a
-- 2010-10-07T09:20:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/tnk-bp-s-barsky-says-will-get-first-look-at-bp-algeria-assets.html
 Russia and India are in talks to
jointly build a new stealth fighter with India, said Russian
Technologies Corp. Chief Executive Officer  Sergei Chemezov .  Russia is also discussing supplying more Su-30 fighters
jets to India, Chemezov told reporters today on Cyprus. State-
owned Russian Technologies controls Rosoboronexport, the
country’s arms exporter.  Russia expects to sign both contracts by year-end, Chemezov
said. He didn’t provide figures.  To contact the reporter on this story:
